{
  "texts": [
    "It could be applied to enhancement of appropriate testing in various ways.",
    "By predicting the amount of information that the repetition of a test provide, ' AI/MLbased MRI' could be considered.",
    "Regarding commonly prescribed pairs (e.g., sodium/chloride), we could think of performing only one of the two tests (e.g., sodium) and predicting the result of the second (in our example, chloride) with AI/ML prediction models.",
    "AI-based clustering of patients could be another way of improving appropriateness of laboratory testing, by defining the most relevant tests to select for each phenotype.",
    "If so, AI/ML-based tools will have to be compliant with the European in vitro diagnostic medical devices regulation (IVDR) [110]."
  ]
}